1 . 'if - else'
The if else block is used to specify the code to be executed if the condition specified in it is true otherwise the else block is executed. 
Example:-

import java.util.Scanner;
public class ifElse{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println(" Please enter the Age ");
        int age = sc.nextInt();
        sc.close();
        if (age > 18) {
            System.out.println("This is an Adult");
        } else {
            System.out.println("This is not an adult");
        }
    }
}

